- Verified reviews refer to reviews made by trusted or verified users.

External knowledge:
- "top-rated" refers to the highest ranked resources based on their ratings and review counts;
- "overall standing" refers to the resource's rank based on its rating and review count;
- "cumulative popularity" refers to the cumulative review count for each city and state;
- "verified" means the resource has been confirmed by the organization;
- "status update" refers to the status message being non-null.

sql:
SELECT amenity_name
FROM amenities
WHERE amenity_id IN (0, 1);
